[Several callers have suggested that this might just be a background case.
If so, this would necessitate an aerosol exposure, which is hard to
imagine, even if reject dirty wool had been used as ceiling or wall
insulation in her house. There has been little livestock anthrax east of
the Mississippi in decades. This possibility would begin to stand up if the
strain identification was other than "Ames" and a strain associated with
imported wools; Oxford is an old mill town. If it is "Ames" it had to be
brought to the deceased woman. - Mod.MHJ
